  "text": "To make the comparison more realistic, we used the same settings as those used by [CITATION_1] . We only used an acceleration sensor as it consumes a low level of power which enables continuous sensing over time and has a long battery life [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In addition, it has has been proven that acceleration sensors are appropriate for activity/position recognition [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . The second important setting is the window length for which we used windows of one-second length and overlap by half, as done in [CITATION_7] .",
